Good afternoon Raffaella

Your privacy request was received on the 1 July 2025 and sent to you by our=
 Privacy Team on the 25 July 2025 and again on the 28 August 2025.
The complete file up to that date was sent to you.



Classification: Sensitive

From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com<mailto:raffaellanz@icloud=
.com>>
Sent: Tuesday, 1 July 2025 11:32 pm

  1.  Privacy Act Request - Full Claim Files:
Under the Privacy Act 2020, I formally request a full copy of my file for b=
oth claims (C90306048 and C90306256). This includes all internal notes, rep=
orts, third-party correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, and any othe=
r material Tower holds in relation to these claims.
The Privacy team has handed on to me the below request from you.

  *   Call recordings/transcripts & communications: Please include any call=
 recordings or transcripts, text/SMS or instant messages, video calls, any =
other forms of communication, and notes from face-to-face meetings.
  *   Simple document index: A single list of everything held on the file (=
date, author, short description) so I can confirm I've received the lot.
  *   Redaction reasons: Where something truly can't be provided, a short r=
eason and, if possible, a partially released copy with only the sensitive b=
its removed.
Call recordings: These were not included in your first request as there was=
 no request for them.
Simple document index: All documents that relate to your personal informati=
on, that are held on your claim file were uploaded to the sharefolder for y=
ou.
You should have received: House - FENZ Report, 2 Assessor reports and claim=
 file notes upto 24 July 2025.  Contents - Asset Restore SOW and claim file=
 notes.
The Privacy Act 2020 establishes the guidelines for disclosing personal inf=
ormation. Personal information is any information which tells us something =
about a specific individual or have the potential to do so.
Redaction reasons;  to protect the privacy of other individuals, company in=
formation, that isn't your personal information.

I note you now have a further Privacy request dated 10 September 2025, I wi=
ll aim to have the file ready to send to you as soon as possible but by the=
 8 October 2025 at the latest.
I will now include all the recorded calls we have on file from you to your =
claims manager.
Assessor reports from the 24 July 2025 and claim file notes from 24 July 20=
25.

Regards
